node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by Apple Hub on August 19, 2021 tagging @atuos_user. May be an image of phone and text that says 'iPhone nano was considered in 2010 @theapplehub Concept from @atuos_ user'.

node.text:
As part of the ongoing legal battle between Apple and Epic Games, an email from Steve Jobs in 2010 has revealed that Apple was considering making an “iPhone nano,” which would have been a miniature version of an iPhone 4. Jobs also mentioned he wanted to create a “low-cost ‌iPhone‌ model based on iPod touch to replace 3GS." Concept from @atuos_user

#Apple #iPhone4 #SteveJobs #iPhonenano #iPhone12 #iPhone13 #Tech #AppleHub

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Apple Hub on August 19, 2021. May be an image of phone and text that says 'iPad with new chip + thinner design coming this fall @theapplehub Apple'.

node.text:
According to Bloomberg’s Mark Gurman, Apple will launch a new iPad (9th generation) this fall with a faster processor (current model features an A12 chip) and a thinner design.

#Apple #iPad #iPad9 #Tech #AppleHub

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by Apple Hub on August 17, 2021 tagging @rendersbyian. May be an image of phone and text.

node.text:
According to Wedbush analyst Daniel Ives, the upcoming iPhone 13 lineup, likely the iPhone 13 Pro models will have a 1TB storage option. Ives also claims the new iPhone models will launch in the third week of September, which would make September 17 the likely release date. Ives also reaffirms that all models will feature a LiDAR sensor, a feature that is currently exclusive to the Pro models. Render from @rendersbyian

#Apple #iPhone12s #iPhone13 #Tech #AppleHub

node.text:
These are the expected models, storage options and prices for the upcoming iPhone lineup. It’s unclear whether Apple will call it the iPhone 12🅂 or iPhone 13.

#Apple #iPhone12s #iPhone13 #Tech #AppleHub

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Apple Hub on August 15, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'Apple Event Apple planning multiple events this Fall @theapplehub Apple'.

node.text:
According to Bloomberg’s Mark Gurman, Apple is planning multiple events for this fall to introduce new iPhones, Apple Watch Series 7, AirPods 3rd gen, iPad mini 6th gen, iPad 9th gen, and redesigned MacBook Pro models. The first event is expected to be held next month. Last year, Apple held three virtual events in September, October and November.

#Apple #iPhone12s #iPhone13 #AirPods #AppleWatch #iPad #iPadmini #MacBookPro #AppleEvent #Tech #AppleHub

node.text:
According to Bloomberg’s Mark Gurman, the upcoming iPhone models will feature more advanced camera features including ProRes for videos (likely exclusive to the Pro models) and Portrait Mode for video. The upcoming iPhone models are expected to launch next month.

#Apple #iPhone12s #iPhone13 #Tech #AppleHub

#Apple #MacBook #MacBookPro #Tech #AppleHub

node.text:

#Apple #MacBook #MacBookAir #Tech #AppleHub

node.text:
Apple has announced that starting with iOS 15 and iPadOS 15, Apple will be able to detect child sexual abuse material images in user’s libraries and report them to the National Center for Missing and Exploited Children (NCMEC). This would only work for images stored in iCloud Photos.

#Apple #iOS15 #iPhone12 #Tech #AppleHub
